defaultRMT, with a large number of other concerned organisat
defaulti
defaultons, wro
defaultte to the Chancellor on 30 May 2013 to outline our opposition to future cuts to bus services.  This letter 
defaultis attached.  It outlines th
defaulte
default fact 
defaultthat 
default“
defaulti
defaultn terms of transport and social inclusion, b
defaultuses offer great value for public money. Nearly 5 billion bus trips are made each year and bus commuters help generate over £64 billion of economic output. Every £1 of public investment in buses provides between £3 and £5 of wider benefits to local economi
defaultes 
defaultas well as
default social and environmental well
default-being. This is a 
